<p>Hagit Benbaji, a philosopher at Ben-Gurion University, has died.</p>
<p><span id="more-54409"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-54411 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/benbaji-hagit-photo.jpg" alt="" width="200" height="172" /></p>
<p><a href="https://in.bgu.ac.il/en/humsos/philosophy/pages/staff/Hagit%20Benbaji.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dr. Benbaji</a> worked mainly in philosophy of mind and metaphysics, writing on pain, colors, the will, and various other topics. You can learn more about her work <a href="https://philpeople.org/profiles/hagit-benbaji" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p>
<p>Benbaji joined the Department of Philosophy at Ben-Gurion University in 2003. Prior to that, she held a visiting scholar position at Princeton University. She earned her PhD (as well as her MA and BA) from Hebrew University of Jerusalem.</p>
<p>She died on July 20th, following a protracted illness.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/07/23/hagit-benbaji-1966-2025/">Hagit Benbaji (1966-2025)</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>